# Thunder engine caches (regenerated)
**/.claude/cache/

# Synthetic benchmark codebases
**/bigdemo/
**/realdemo/
**/ngdemo/
**/pydemo/
**/nodedemo/
**/reactdemo/

# Maven build output
**/target/

# Node
node_modules/

# Thunder DEBUG trace + per-framework debug config (.thunder/<fw>/.config) — local toggles, generated
**/.thunder/gains.md
**/.thunder/*/.config

# Framework index now COMMITTED under .thunder/<lang>/ (project-brief, index, shards, cards,
# capability-map, routes/endpoints, functional.json) so two devs SHARE it on a branch and don't
# re-spend tokens re-inferring the functional layer. Only the per-dev VOLATILE bits stay ignored:
**/.thunder/*/cache.ndjson
**/.thunder/*/manifest.json
**/.thunder/*/dirty.list
**/.thunder/*/qa-ledger.ndjson

# This repo's own framework demos are fixtures — don't commit their generated index (no functional
# layer here anyway; it needs the cartographer agent). The committed-index behavior is for real projects.
plugins/thunder-*/demo/.thunder/

# thunder-mind: .thunder/mind/decisions/ is the COMMITTED source of truth; the derived index lives in
# .claude/cache/thunder-mind/ (covered by **/.claude/cache/ above). Ignore the synthetic scaling corpus.
plugins/thunder-mind/minddemo-big/
